review.body:
@auturgy the approach I used to disable development messages in release builds is to exclude them via ifdef: https://github.com/mavlink/qgroundcontrol/pull/10788/commits/489a03bbc1bb02fce06d2e5f9920bf33d5b80e3a. We'll need to replicated that in cmake, at the latest when switching away from qmake.
There's other approaches, like using a different dialect for release builds (which also requires ifdefs), or making it a runtime option.
Either one works for me. I find the runtime option interesting, as it allows users who are ok with potential risk of breakage to still use the functionality.
